WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.735
Two very different tickets sound identical.

p02
00:00:01.735 --> 00:00:03.474
It keeps logging me out.

p03
00:00:03.474 --> 00:00:04.619
My screen froze.

p04
00:00:04.619 --> 00:00:10.622
Most of the time, the first one is the idle timeout doing exactly what it's set to do.

p05
00:00:10.622 --> 00:00:14.960
So before you open a single setting, decide which of the two you're actually chasing.

p06
00:00:15.394 --> 00:00:16.634
Here's the warning itself.

p07
00:00:16.634 --> 00:00:21.506
After a stretch of no activity, a dialog counts down from two minutes,

p08
00:00:21.506 --> 00:00:23.985
and a matching toast slides into the corner.

p09
00:00:23.985 --> 00:00:25.832
One click keeps them in.

p10
00:00:25.832 --> 00:00:28.311
So does a nudge of the mouse.

p11
00:00:28.311 --> 00:00:32.571
Walk away and let it reach zero, and that's not a fault.

p12
00:00:32.571 --> 00:00:35.360
It's the platform closing an idle station on purpose.

p13
00:00:35.830 --> 00:00:37.284
Now the first real check.

p14
00:00:37.284 --> 00:00:41.344
Open System Users and search for the person by name or code.

p15
00:00:41.344 --> 00:00:44.659
The column you want is their user level.

p16
00:00:44.659 --> 00:00:48.580
It's a single word, but it decides everything on the next page.

p17
00:00:48.580 --> 00:00:50.617
Don't scroll the list hunting for them.

p18
00:00:50.617 --> 00:00:50.907
Search.

p19
00:00:51.460 --> 00:00:53.702
One caution before you trust a blank screen.

p20
00:00:54.536 --> 00:00:58.427
If the list won't load and you see a note about the connection to the agent service,

p21
00:00:58.743 --> 00:00:59.910
the rows aren't missing.

p22
00:01:00.245 --> 00:01:01.636
The data just didn't arrive.

p23
00:01:02.423 --> 00:01:05.198
And if that's what your caller is staring at instead of a logout, it's a different problem:

p24
00:01:05.547 --> 00:01:09.012
the data service, not the timeout.

p25
00:01:09.571 --> 00:01:11.238
Second check, second page.

p26
00:01:11.763 --> 00:01:16.726
User Levels lives under Automation, not with the other user pages, which trips people up.

p27
00:01:17.285 --> 00:01:20.147
Once you're there, one column answers the whole ticket: session timeout, in minutes.

p28
00:01:20.454 --> 00:01:25.778
That's how long a level can sit idle before the countdown starts.

p29
00:01:26.402 --> 00:01:28.612
Read that number against the level you found.

p30
00:01:28.942 --> 00:01:31.829
They run from five minutes up to a hundred and twenty.

p31
00:01:32.453 --> 00:01:35.703
Cashiers and the other short-timeout roles sit at five,

p32
00:01:35.983 --> 00:01:40.802
so a cashier who steps away for five minutes gets the warning, then the logout.

p33
00:01:41.167 --> 00:01:42.424
Nothing is broken.

p34
00:01:42.633 --> 00:01:44.585
Someone set it that way on purpose.

p35
00:01:45.244 --> 00:01:47.609
If the timing matches that number, you're done.

p36
00:01:47.609 --> 00:01:53.217
Tell them it's a setting for their role, not a glitch, and show them the fix:

p37
00:01:53.217 --> 00:01:57.675
move the mouse, press a key, or click Stay Logged In.

p38
00:01:57.675 --> 00:02:01.916
If the role truly needs longer, an admin can raise it in production.

p39
00:02:01.916 --> 00:02:02.508
One warning.

p40
00:02:02.508 --> 00:02:05.168
Don't tap Log Out Now to clear the box.

p41
00:02:05.168 --> 00:02:07.430
That ends the session for real.

p42
00:02:07.430 --> 00:02:09.003
Now the cases that are real.

p43
00:02:09.799 --> 00:02:14.487
Logged out well before the level allows, or frozen with no warning at all.

p44
00:02:15.306 --> 00:02:16.925
First, rule out the simple thing:

p45
00:02:17.129 --> 00:02:19.883
a session is tied to one device and one browser, so switching either signs you out by design.

p46
00:02:20.174 --> 00:02:22.860
If it still doesn't add up, capture the level, its set timeout, and the time it really took,

p47
00:02:23.458 --> 00:02:28.346
and send that to support with the username, never a password.

p48
00:02:28.641 --> 00:02:31.734
The trigger point for the demo login is still parked,

p49
00:02:32.289 --> 00:02:37.360
so measure it before you promise a number.

